{
  "texts": [
    "Excluding toxic response, response pairs are given to Llama2-chat and labeled either chosen or rejected.",
    "Note that if both responses are considered preferred or not preferred, we dropped out corresponding data.",
    "This decision was made to maintain the integrity and relevance of the data in our study.",
    "In our experiments, the base model used was Llama2 with 7 billion parameters, which is opensource and permitted for research purpose, attached with LoRA (Hu et al., 2021) adaptor at a rank of 16, and the alpha parameter was set to 32.",
    "During the SFT phase, we utilized 40% of the Anthropic dataset, reserving the remaining 60% for generating preference data in both the DPO and ADPO training."
  ]
}